President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Missouri due to severe storms, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred starting on April 29, 2019. This declaration allows for Federal funding to supplement State and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Assistance can include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for property losses, and other programs to aid individuals and business owners in recovering from the disaster. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has appointed Seamus K. Leary as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance online or by phone. Further information can be obtained by contacting the FEMA News Desk.